                                           UserException
        Web Method to get list of accounts for user connected with sessionId in webService context
        Returns:
        List of accounts from database
        Throws:
        SessionException - Exception when there is no user for sessionId from context
        UserException - Exception thrown when user assigned to session not exists anymore

      • depositMoney

        public Operation depositMoney(java.lang.String title,
                              java.lang.String amount,
                              java.lang.String targetAccountNumber)
                       throws NotValidException,
                              SessionException,
                              UserException,
                              OperationException,
                              AccountServiceException,
                              TaxInspectorException
        Web Method to deposit money on account
        Parameters:
        title - Title of deposit if user wants to have his own titles
        amount - Amount in pennies
        targetAccountNumber - Account number to target account
        Returns:
        Operation object if created and succeeded
        Throws:
        NotValidException - Exception if params not valid
        SessionException - Exception thrown when user is not logged in or session has expired
        UserException - Exception thrown when user assigned to session not exists anymore
        OperationException - In this case never thrown because deposit with valid data always succeeded
        AccountServiceException - Exception thrown if targetAccount doesn't exists
        TaxInspectorException - Exception when amount is way bigger than allowed

      • withdrawMoney

        public Operation withdrawMoney(java.lang.String title,

                               java.lang.String targetAccountNumber)
                        throws NotValidException,
                               SessionException,
                               UserException,
                               OperationException,
                               AccountServiceException,
                               TaxInspectorException
        Web Method to withdraw money from account
        Parameters:
        title - Title of deposit if user wants to have his own titles
        amount - Amount in pennies
        targetAccountNumber - Account number to target account
        Returns:
        Operation object if created and succeeded
        Throws:
        NotValidException - Exception if params not valid
        SessionException - Exception thrown when user is not logged in or session has expired
        UserException - Exception thrown when user assigned to session not exists anymore
        OperationException - Exception when amount is more than balance on account
        AccountServiceException - Exception thrown if targetAccount doesn't exists
        TaxInspectorException - Exception when amount is way bigger than allowed

      • getBankFeeFromAccount

        public Operation getBankFeeFromAccount(java.lang.String targetAccountNumber)
                                throws NotValidException,
                                       SessionException,
                                       UserException,
                                       OperationException,
                                       AccountServiceException,
                                       AccountChecksumException,
                                       TaxInspectorException
        Web method to get bank fee from account
        Parameters:
        targetAccountNumber - Account to charge money
        Returns:
        Operation if succeed
        Throws:
        NotValidException - Exception if params not valid
        SessionException - Exception thrown when user is not logged in or session has expired
        UserException - Exception thrown when user assigned to session not exists anymore
        OperationException - Never thrown in this case. Bank always get what he wants.
        AccountServiceException - Exception if targetAccount doesn't exists
        AccountChecksumException - Exception if checksum of account not valid
        TaxInspectorException - Never thrown in this case

      • transferMoney

        public Operation transferMoney(java.lang.String title,
                               java.lang.String amount,
                               java.lang.String sourceAccountNumber,
                               java.lang.String targetAccountNumber)
                        throws NotValidException,
                               SessionException,
                               UserException,
                               AccountServiceException,
                               OperationException,
                               AccountException,
                               java.io.IOException,
                               TaxInspectorException
        Web method to transfer money
        Parameters:
        title - Title of transfer
        amount - Amount of transfer in string, needed to be parsed to int
        sourceAccountNumber - Account from we want transfer
        targetAccountNumber - Account to we want to transfer
        Returns:
        Operation object if success
        Throws:
        NotValidException - Exception if params not valid
        SessionException - Exception thrown when user is not logged in or session has expired
        UserException - Exception thrown when user assigned to session not exists anymore
        AccountServiceException - Exception thrown when transfer and source account are the same, target bank doesn't exists if ELIXIR transfer
        OperationException - Exception thrown if operation succeed
        AccountException - Exception thrown if source account doesn't exists and if internal transfer if targetAccount doesn't exists
        java.io.IOException
        TaxInspectorException - Exception when amount to transfer is way bigger than allowed
